		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span>Get ready, Wildcats — this summer is about to explode!<span><br/></span>August 6th to 9th, 2026<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Book by<span><br/></span>DAVID SIMPATICO<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span>Songs by<span><br/></span>Matthew Gerrard and Robbie Nevil; Ray Cham, Greg Cham and Andrew Seeley;<span><br/></span>Randy Petersen and Kevin Quinn; Andy Dodd and Adam Watts; Bryan Louiselle;<span><br/></span>David N. Lawrence and Faye Greenberg; Jamie Houston<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span>Music Adapted, Arranged and Produced by<span><br/></span>Bryan Louiselle<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span>Based on a Disney Channel Original Movie Written by<span><br/></span>Peter Barsocchini<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">DISNEY'S HIGH SCHOOL MUSICAL</span><span><br/></span>​A Huge Summer Bash at the KCT<span><br/></span>This isn’t just a show.<span><br/></span>This is a full-throttle, sun-soaked, joy-blasting SUMMER EVENT—and it’s landing at the KCT like a confetti cannon.<span><br/></span>​<span><br/></span>Pixie & Dot Productions, Sassafras & Co., Too Fly Productions & Blind Faith Productions are teaming up for an electrifying co-production of Disney's High School Musical, celebrating the 20th anniversary of the iconic movie that defined a generation. Two decades later, the music still slaps, the friendships still hit, and the energy? Bigger than ever.<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span>This production is built to be a spectacle.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Think bold choreography. Large ensemble moments. Pop-rock vocals that lift the roof. A stage bursting with colour, movement, and summer magic. It’s nostalgia turned up to eleven—reimagined for today’s audiences, families, teens, and anyone who still knows every word to Breaking Free.<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span>Whether you grew up with the Wildcats or you’re discovering East High for the first time, this is your invitation to: Sing louder / Dance harder / Bop to the top.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>From first note to final bow, Disney's High School Musical at the KCT will be a high-energy celebration of friendship, ambition, and going after what lights you up—together.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Big cast<span><br/></span>Big moves<span><br/></span>Big summer vibes</span><span><br/></span>​<span><br/></span>This is the summer bash everyone will be talking about.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>This is the anniversary event you don’t want to miss.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>This is Disney's High School Musical—big, bold, and bursting onto the stage this summer.<span><br/></span> <span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">We’re all in. Are you?</span></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">ALL AGES - FAMILY FUN!</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">RUNNING TIME:</span> 2hrs with a 20min intermission<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>​---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Pricing</h2><span class=\"BoldText\">Adult (19+) $62.74</span>  ($52.50 base price + $2.36 CIF + $7.88 service charge)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Senior (55+)  $49.45</span>  ($40.95 base price + $2.36 CIF + $6.14 service charge)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Student $49.45</span>  ($40.95 base price + $2.36 CIF + $6.14 service charge)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All above prices are in CAD and include GST.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Kelowna Community Theatre event tickets include a $2.25 Capital Improvement Fee (CIF) and 5% GST. A service fee is added for box office costs, card processing, and taxes. <span class=\"BoldText\">Disney's High School Musical</span> tickets and their applicable service fees are non-refundable.</span>
""";
