<http://www.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/event/384201AMSKMRNDBSCVBSHSCRLDJTTHGQR>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Hokus Pokus Live!";
  schema:description """
	<table class=\" BorderOn\">
		<tr>
			<td align=\"left\" colspan=\"1\"><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/files/aae395fa-3af9-4d14-966a-337ae28dd497.jpg\" /> </td><td align=\"left\"><h2>Fruit Wine Productions and OBSESSED present </h2><h1><span class=\"UnderlineText\">HOKUS POKUS LIVE!</span></h1></td>
		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">All ages. This show may contain adult themes and language.</span></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Get ready to run amok, amok, amok! The witches are back and confused about what is happening in this new world of 2026! Hokus Pokus Live! is a hilarious, high-camp parody of everyone’s favorite Halloween cult classic, brought to life by drag royalty. With the power of Magica Mystica, Salem’s most infamous and glamorous trio is resurrected from the grave for one night only. Be wary; they are willing to attack and suck the life force out of everyone in their way to stay young, beautiful, and alive forever! This all live singing, fully scripted theatrical experience is unlike any other show you've ever seen! <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">ARTIST BIOS:</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Ginger Minj:</span> Originally hailing from small town Leesburg, Florida, Ginger Minj made her first splash on the global stage as a finalist on RuPaul’s Drag Race Season 7. As a fan favorite and triple threat she was invited back for Drag Race All Stars 2 and made it to the top 3 of All Stars 6 and the winner of RuPaul's Drag Race All Stars 10! She has starred in the Anne Fletcher helmed “Dumplin” for Netflix alongside Jennifer Aniston and Dove Cameron, in the Netflix series “AJ & The Queen”, and most recently in the Disney + Original Movie, “Hocus Pocus 2” and now in Bleeker Streets Stop! That! Train! When she is not touring the world or appearing in movies and live theatrical shows, Ginger can be heard on her three studio albums, Sweet T, Gummybear and Double Wide Diva! Her first book, Southern Fried Sass, is now available anywhere you buy books.<span><br/></span>Instagram @GingerMinj<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Jujubee:</span> Best known for appearances on RuPaul’s Drag Race. Jujubee rediscovered their love of live theatre with their critically acclaimed performance of “Summer Raines” in “Death Drop” in London’s West End, “Sister Maria Julie Andrews” in the UK Tour of “Death Drop: Back in the Habit,” starred as “Madame” in “Cinderella” at North Shore Music Theatre and, most recently, “The Tigress” in “Drag The Musical” at New World Stages making their Off Broadway debut. Jujubee released two EP’S titled “Good Juju” volumes 1 and 2 which peaked at #1 and #7 on the iTunes singer/songwriter charts.<span><br/></span>Follow Jujubee: @jujubeeonline on IG, @officialjujubee on TIKTOK and @jujubeefans on Facebook.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Sapphira Cristàl:</span> Sapphira Cristál (runner-up and Miss Congeniality of RuPaul’s Drag Race season 16) is a classically trained opera singer, composer, and drag queen known for her theatrical lip syncs and six-octave range. She is renowned as a charismatic host who forges a special connection with her audiences. Sapphira holds 16 pageant crowns and has performed globally. Philadelphia magazine named her 2023's Best Drag Queen Who Actually Sings. In 2024, Sapphira was thrice the guest artist in Madonna’s Celebration Tour, and she debuted her original operatic production, Soundcake, with Monét X Change and Thorgy Thor at Lincoln Center. Afterward, she brought her one-woman show, The Cristál Ball Tour, across North America. Since then, she has toured her stand-up comedy show, One Slue Over the Cuckoo's Nest, across the U.S.; appeared at New York City's famed 54 Below; and starred in  RuPaul's Drag Race Live! in Las Vegas.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Landon Cider:</span> Landon Cider has been proving Drag Kings can reign just as fierce as Queens for over 16 years. The Season 3 Winner of “Boulet Brothers Dragula” has broken many glass ceilings in his career and has appeared on HBO, MTV, VH1, Netflix & Hulu. He became a permanent judge on S2 of “Call Me Mother”, a recurring judge on “Dragula”, and having most recently guest judged on “King of Drag” the world’s first Drag King Competition. He has one favor for you today: next time you attend a Drag show and there are only Queens in the cast, ask the producer “WhereTF are the KINGS?!”<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Fruit Wine Productions:</span> a queer-owned and operated multimedia production company dedicated to elevating drag and LGBTQ+ entertainment through high-quality, fully scripted theatrical performances and engaging digital content. They have produced such hits as The Golden Gals Live!, Hokus Pokus Live!, The Munsterz, and so many others! Follow them @fruitwineproductions on all socials or visit FruitWineProductions.com<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">All ages. This show may contain adult themes and language.</span></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">VIP Upgrade packages available!</span> <span><br/></span>(You <span class=\"UnderlineText\">must</span> purchase a show ticket in order to purchase a VIP upgrade! The VIP upgrade does NOT include a show ticket!)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>For the Coven Ultra Upgrade Package, click <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.theboxoffice.ca/upcoming-events/hokus-pokus-live-coven-ultra-vip-upgrade-package\">here!</a><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>For the RIP (Really Important Person) Upgrade Package, click <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.theboxoffice.ca/upcoming-events/hokus-pokus-live-rip-really-important-person-upgrade-package\">here!</a><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Pricing</h2><span class=\"BoldText\">Tier 1  $87.44</span>  ($73.98 base price + $2.36 CIF + $11.10 service charge)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Tier 2  $75.37</span>  ($63.48 base price + $2.36 CIF + $9.53 service charge)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Tier 3  $63.29</span>  ($52.98 base price + $2.36 CIF + $7.95 service charge)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Tier 4  $39.14</span>  ($31.98 base price + $2.36 CIF + $4.80 service charge)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Tier 5  $20.00</span>  ($15.01 base price + $2.36 CIF + $2.63 service charge)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All above prices are in CAD and include GST.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Kelowna Community Theatre event tickets include a $2.36 Capital Improvement Fee (CIF). A service fee is added for box office costs, card processing, and taxes. <span class=\"BoldText\">Hokus Pokus Live!</span> tickets and service fees are non-refundable.</span>
""";
