<http://www.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/event/388201ADMPSKLCMBTGPSDNGSLNLMKKDLM>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "RCA Presents - CaneFire";
  schema:description """
	<table class=\" BorderOn\">
		<tr>
			<td align=\"left\" colspan=\"1\"><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/files/aaee1062-2dc1-4eba-bcfa-0c1fa59bcb5c.jpg\" /> </td><td align=\"left\"><h2>Rotary Centre for the Arts presents </h2><h1><span class=\"UnderlineText\">CANEFIRE</span></h1></td>
		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span>As one of the most explosive and energetic jazz ensembles on the planet, CaneFire delivers a rollicking, high-octane show combining the white-hot energy of Cuban rhythm, the blinding musicianship of modern jazz, and the unbridled joy of the music of the Caribbean.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Led by Canadian pianist/composer Jeremy Ledbetter, CaneFire also features steelpan virtuoso Mark Mosca, Alexis Baro (trumpet), Braxton Hicks (saxophones), Chendy Leon (drums), Yoser Rodriguez (bass), and Alberto Suarez (percussion). CaneFire’s signature sound revolves around its unconventional use of the steelpan – the only petroleum byproduct in the world that is actually good for you.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>CaneFire has released two albums and taken their unique brand of Caribbean Latin Jazz from BC to Newfoundland, to South America, and to the Caribbean, including three years in a row at the Trinidad and Tobago Jazz Festival. Their second album, Pandemonium, embodies all the sizzle and twice the sophistication of its predecessor and features guest performances by Trinidadian calypso superstar David Rudder and Brazilian jazz legend Hermeto Pascoal.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>To learn more about CaneFire, visit <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://www.canefire.ca/\">canefire.ca</a>.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Pricing</h2><span class=\"BoldText\">Adult  $63.09</span>  ($52.50 base price + $2.36 CIF + $8.23 service charge)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Student w/ID  $32.90</span>  ($26.25 base price + $2.36 CIF + $4.29 service charge)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All above prices include GST.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Mary Irwin Theatre at the Rotary Centre for the Arts event tickets include a $2.36 Capital Improvement Fee (CIF). A service fee is added for box office costs, card processing, and taxes. <span class=\"BoldText\">CaneFire</span> tickets and their applicable fees are non-refundable.</span><span><br/></span>
""";
