<http://www.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/event/385801ALPTPDQDKNGDJJTHCQGJSQNLLHQ>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "RCA Presents - Rémi Bolduc Jazz Ensemble";
  schema:description """
	<table class=\" BorderOn\">
		<tr>
			<td align=\"left\" colspan=\"1\"><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/files/7099fb7d-6f62-4b7e-8834-ed41806555f8.jpg\" /> </td><td align=\"left\"><h2>Rotary Centre for the Arts presents </h2><h1><span class=\"UnderlineText\">RÉMI BOLDUC JAZZ ENSEMBLE</span></h1></td>
		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span>Alto saxophone master Rémi Bolduc highlights the greatest jazz classics, Christmas songs, and lesser-known tunes, adding his \"blue\" touch to them to the delight of jazz lovers. Christmas + jazz classics = a perfect evening!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Rémi Bolduc is a highly accomplished and respected jazz saxophonist and educator with notable musicians with over 40 years of experience in the music industry. He is an associate professor at the Schulich School of Music at McGill University in Montreal.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>As a musician, Bolduc has released 11 jazz albums, featuring collaborations with notable musicians such as Kenny Werner, Marc Johnson, Ben Wonder, and Jerry Bergonzi. He has also designed three saxophone models for the Expression company, which bear his name.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>To learn more about Rémi Bolduc, visit <a target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://remibolduc.com\">remibolduc.com</a>.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Sponsored by Cristalina PARC.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Pricing</h2><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Adult  $54.64</span>  ($45.15 base price + $2.36 CIF + $7.13 service charge)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Student w/ID  $32.90</span>  ($26.25 base price + $2.36 CIF + $4.29 service charge)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All above prices include GST.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Mary Irwin Theatre at the Rotary Centre for the Arts event tickets include a $2.36 Capital Improvement Fee (CIF). A service fee is added for box office costs, card processing, and taxes. <span class=\"BoldText\">Rémi Bolduc Jazz Ensemble</span> tickets and their applicable fees are non-refundable.</span><span><br/></span>
""";
