<http://www.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/event/368601AJJCGSTMQJKSQVNTLBLKGLMQRSN>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Steph Tolev";
  schema:description """
	<table class=\" BorderOn\">
		<tr>
			<td align=\"left\" colspan=\"1\"><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/files/4f38fabd-07db-4e95-97ca-d1fd377ee415.jpg\" /> </td><td align=\"left\"><h2>Live Nation presents </h2><h1><span class=\"UnderlineText\">STEPH TOLEV</span></h1></td>
		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">This event is for ages 18 and up.</span></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Comedian and actress <span class=\"BoldText\">Steph Tolev</span>’s debut hour special <span class=\"ItalicText\">FILTH QUEEN</span> premiered on Netflix June 24th, produced by Bill Burr. Steph also appeared as “Barb” in the second season of Shane Gillis’ Netflix series <span class=\"ItalicText\">TIRES</span>. Steph’s no-holds-barred and unfiltered comedy made her a perfect choice to host the 2025 <span class=\"ItalicText\">AVN AWARDS</span> in Las Vegas earlier this year, the first female comedian to host in a decade. Following the year she’s had, Steph was just selected as one of 2025’s <span class=\"ItalicText\">VARIEY COMICS TO WATCH</span>. Steph first broke with a standout set in Burr’s “BILL BURR PRESENTS: FRIENDS WHO KILL” Netflix special, also featuring comics Michelle Wolf, Jimmy Carr, Dave Attell, Ronny Chieng, and more. She had a scene stealing role in Burr’s 2023 Netflix film OLD DADS and played herself during Deborah Vance’s roast on HBOMax’s HACKS. Tolev has headlined across the country on her FILTH QUEEN and KEEPIN ‘EM HARD tours and is a regular/favorite at LA’s Comedy Store.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Pricing</h2><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Tier 1  $61.59</span>  ($51.50 base price + $2.36 CIF + $7.73 service charge)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Tier 2  $50.09</span>  ($41.50 base price + $2.36 CIF + $6.23 service charge)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Tier 3  $38.59</span>  ($31.50 base price + $2.36 CIF + $4.73 service charge)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">VIP  $130.79</span>  ($111.50 base price + $2.36 CIF + $16.73 service charge)<span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">VIP includes a post-show Meet & Greet, and an exclusive piece of merch</span></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All above prices are in CAD and include GST.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Kelowna Community Theatre event tickets include a $2.36 Capital Improvement Fee (CIF). A service fee is added for box office costs, card processing, and taxes. <span class=\"BoldText\">Steph Tolev</span> tickets and service fees are non-refundable.</span>
""";
