<http://www.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/event/389401ALTDPTKQJHSCSRGBRNTTMJQNPQD>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Train Wreck Comedy Concert Series - Dan Smith";
  schema:description """
	<table class=\" BorderOn\">
		<tr>
			<td align=\"left\" colspan=\"1\"><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/files/973dc8d4-27e7-472d-b8ae-3e6e00620ae9.jpg\" /> </td><td align=\"left\"><h2>Train Wreck Comedy Concert Series presents </h2><h1><span class=\"UnderlineText\">DAN SMITH</span></h1><h2>presented by Freddy's Brewpub</h2></td>
		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Dan Smith</span> hit the ground running in comedy, winning HBO’s <span class=\"ItalicText\">Funniest Comic in Boston</span> competition in his very first year as a stand-up comedian. Riding that momentum, Dan packed up and headed to Los Angeles, where he quickly built an impressive career both on stage and behind the scenes in television and entertainment. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>As a performer, Dan has appeared on numerous television programs including <span class=\"ItalicText\">The Drew Carey Show, Talk Soup, Loco Comedy Jam, Star Search</span>, and his own comedy special on the Starz Network. His sharp writing talents also earned him success behind the camera, writing and producing for hit shows such as <span class=\"ItalicText\">Blind Date</span>, <span class=\"ItalicText\">The 5th Wheel</span>, and <span class=\"ItalicText\">Ex-Treme Dating</span>. For more than four years, Dan was also a joke writer for <span class=\"ItalicText\">Us Weekly Magazine</span> as part of the popular “Fashion Police” team. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>On stage, Dan has toured alongside some of comedy’s biggest names including George Lopez, Bob Saget, Bill Burr, and Rob Schneider, earning a reputation as a seasoned and versatile headliner. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Perhaps most impressively, Dan has completed more than 25 military comedy tours — and counting — performing for U.S. and NATO troops in over 35 countries around the world. His travels have taken him everywhere from Bosnia, Kosovo, Iceland, Japan, and Korea to Kuwait, Saudi Arabia, Afghanistan, and Iraq. In recognition of his dedication and performances overseas, Dan has received more than 250 Certificates of Appreciation from military organizations worldwide. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Beyond clubs and theaters, Dan is also a highly sought-after corporate entertainer, with hundreds of company parties, charity fundraisers, and special events to his credit. His client list includes New Balance, Cisco Systems, Habitat for Humanity, The Lance Armstrong Foundation, Home Depot, the Los Angeles Police and Fire Departments, the Worcester Police Department, the USO, and many more. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>With a unique blend of sharp writing, world-class stage experience, and effortless likability, Dan Smith continues to entertain audiences everywhere he performs.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Pricing</h2><span class=\"BoldText\">Regular  $65.00</span>  ($54.16 base price + $2.36 CIF + $8.48 service charge)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All above prices are CAD and include GST.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">The Train Wreck Comedy Concert Series is bringing five unforgettable nights of world-class stand-up comedy to the Rotary Centre for the Arts, featuring some of the funniest professional comedians from across North America. <span class=\"BoldText\">Freddy’s Brewpub is proud to be the Official Beer Sponsor</span> of the series, serving great local craft beer at all five performances while audiences enjoy razor-sharp storytelling, side-splitting crowd work, huge energy, big personalities, and nonstop laughs.  Whether you're a die-hard comedy fan or just looking for an incredible night out, this is the must-see comedy event series of the year!</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Mary Irwin Theatre at the Rotary Centre for the Arts event tickets include a $2.36 Capital Improvement Fee (CIF). A service fee is added for box office costs, card processing, and taxes. <span class=\"BoldText\">Dan Smith</span> tickets and their applicable fees are non-refundable.</span>
""";
