<http://www.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/event/389601ABNCHLNLJQNNRGNGLPRJMGHMBRG>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Train Wreck Comedy Concert Series - Dave Hemstad";
  schema:description """
	<table class=\" BorderOn\">
		<tr>
			<td align=\"left\" colspan=\"1\"><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/files/26707162-c2ea-456b-a604-448b383b7699.jpg\" /> </td><td align=\"left\"><h2>Train Wreck Comedy Concert Series presents </h2><h1><span class=\"UnderlineText\">DAVE HEMSTAD</span></h1><h2>presented by Blair Tactical</h2></td>
		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span>Born and raised in Thornhill, Ontario, <span class=\"BoldText\">Dave Hemstad</span> was once an Academic All-American golfer with a promising future on the fairways — until a lightning strike literally changed the course of his life. Swapping birdies for belly laughs, Dave has spent the last 20 years touring the globe with his signature brand of clean, razor-sharp comedy that brilliantly finds humor in the everyday moments we all experience. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>A true triple threat as a stand-up comedian, writer, and actor, Dave has become one of Canada’s most respected comedic voices. He’s appeared at some of the country’s top comedy festivals including Just For Laughs, the Halifax Comedy Festival, and the Winnipeg Comedy Festival, while also starring in his own <span class=\"ItalicText\">Comedy Now!</span> special. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Fans across Canada also know Dave as a beloved regular on CBC Radio’s <span class=\"ItalicText\">The Debaters</span>, where his quick wit and polished storytelling have made him a standout favorite. Behind the scenes, Dave has built an impressive writing career, contributing to shows such as <span class=\"ItalicText\">Still Standing</span> and the Canadian Screen Awards hosted by Norm Macdonald. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>On screen, Dave’s acting credits include appearances in <span class=\"ItalicText\">Almost Heroes</span> and CBS Sports’ <span class=\"ItalicText\">Off The Hozzle</span>, further showcasing his versatility as a performer. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>When he’s not touring stages across North America, Dave co-hosts the hit podcast <span class=\"ItalicText\">Dr. Val Saves Dave</span>, and his latest comedy album, <span class=\"ItalicText\">DAD INTENTIONS</span>, is streaming everywhere. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Smart, relatable, and effortlessly funny, Dave Hemstad continues to win over audiences with comedy that’s as clean as it is hilarious.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Pricing</h2><span class=\"BoldText\">Regular  $65.00</span>  ($54.16 base price + $2.36 CIF + $8.48 service charge)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All above prices are CAD and include GST.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">The Train Wreck Comedy Concert Series is bringing five unforgettable nights of world-class stand-up comedy to the Rotary Centre for the Arts, featuring some of the funniest professional comedians from across North America. <span class=\"BoldText\">Freddy’s Brewpub is proud to be the Official Beer Sponsor</span> of the series, serving great local craft beer at all five performances while audiences enjoy razor-sharp storytelling, side-splitting crowd work, huge energy, big personalities, and nonstop laughs.  Whether you're a die-hard comedy fan or just looking for an incredible night out, this is the must-see comedy event series of the year!</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Mary Irwin Theatre at the Rotary Centre for the Arts event tickets include a $2.36 Capital Improvement Fee (CIF). A service fee is added for box office costs, card processing, and taxes. <span class=\"BoldText\">Dave Hemstad</span> tickets and their applicable fees are non-refundable.</span>
""";
