<http://www.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/event/387001ASGVHBBDVPLPDDSHPNNRRQCNRKH>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Train Wreck Comedy Concert Series - Dino Archie's K-Town Comedy Extravaganza";
  schema:description """
	<table class=\" BorderOn\">
		<tr>
			<td align=\"left\" colspan=\"1\"><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/files/896f6d0c-8349-4e87-9ad7-482769eebfbc.jpg\" /> </td><td align=\"left\"><h2>Train Wreck Comedy Concert Series presents </h2><h1><span class=\"UnderlineText\">DINO ARCHIE'S K-TOWN COMEDY EXTRAVAGANZA</span></h1><h2>presented by Freddy's Brewpub</h2></td>
		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Dino Archie</span> - Originally from Fresno, California, Dino Archie is one of stand-up comedy’s most naturally funny and charismatic performers. Now based in Vancouver, Dino has appeared on Comedy Central’s <span class=\"ItalicText\">Adam Devine’s House Party</span> and <span class=\"ItalicText\">Jimmy Kimmel Live!</span>, while earning recognition as a Just For Laughs New Face, Seattle International Comedy Competition winner, and Best Crowd Work winner at Just For Laughs Northwest and Kevin Hart’s LOL Network. His credits also include NPR’s <span class=\"ItalicText\">Snap Judgment</span>, <span class=\"ItalicText\">Don’t Tell Comedy</span>, Crave’s Russell Peters Gala, CBC Gem Originals, and Amazon Prime’s <span class=\"ItalicText\">Inside Jokes</span>. With laid-back confidence and razor-sharp crowd work, Dino makes every show feel unforgettable. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Brett Forte</span> - Brett Forte is one of Canada’s fastest-rising comedy exports, earning titles like Yuk Yuk’s Top New Comic and Edmonton’s Funniest Person before being selected as a Just For Laughs New Face in 2019. A favorite at the Hollywood Comedy Festival, Brett has appeared on <span class=\"ItalicText\">The Fighter and The Kid</span>, <span class=\"ItalicText\">Joke WRLD</span>, and <span class=\"ItalicText\">The Uncle Lazer Podcas</span>t. After nearly a decade headlining across Canada, Brett now lives in Austin, Texas — supposedly for comedy, though there may also be a warrant involved. Known for fearless storytelling and unpredictable energy, Brett now headlines clubs across the U.S. including The Hollywood Improv, Phoenix House of Comedy, and Hyena’s Comedy Clubs. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Nacya Marreiro</span> - Originally from the south of Portugal, Nacya Marreiro is a fast-rising comedian, actress, and writer bringing fearless energy and sharp perspective to stages around the world. After discovering stand-up while working as a flight attendant, she quickly built an international career performing at top clubs including The Comedy Store, Hollywood Improv, Laugh Factory, The Stand NYC, and Vulcan Austin. Nacya is the creator of <span class=\"ItalicText\">The Riff</span> at the Hollywood Improv and host of the YouTube comedy cooking series <span class=\"ItalicText\">Mouth Full</span>. She has released her own comedy special, starred in the Amazon Prime film <span class=\"ItalicText\">Moving Valentine</span>, and regularly features for The Lucas Brothers throughout the U.S. and Canada. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Pricing</h2><span class=\"BoldText\">Regular  $65.00</span>  ($54.16 base price + $2.36 CIF + $8.48 service charge)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All above prices are CAD and include GST.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">The Train Wreck Comedy Concert Series is bringing five unforgettable nights of world-class stand-up comedy to the Rotary Centre for the Arts, featuring some of the funniest professional comedians from across North America. <span class=\"BoldText\">Freddy’s Brewpub is proud to be the Official Beer Sponsor</span> of the series, serving great local craft beer at all five performances while audiences enjoy razor-sharp storytelling, side-splitting crowd work, huge energy, big personalities, and nonstop laughs.  Whether you're a die-hard comedy fan or just looking for an incredible night out, this is the must-see comedy event series of the year!</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Mary Irwin Theatre at the Rotary Centre for the Arts event tickets include a $2.36 Capital Improvement Fee (CIF). A service fee is added for box office costs, card processing, and taxes. <span class=\"BoldText\">Dino Archie's Extravaganza</span> tickets and their applicable fees are non-refundable.</span>
""";
