<http://www.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/event/389201ATVLNPNGBLNGKBNNMMKTJCKKNBS>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Train Wreck Comedy Concert Series - Kelly Taylor";
  schema:description """
	<table class=\" BorderOn\">
		<tr>
			<td align=\"left\" colspan=\"1\"><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/files/a16faabf-77b0-47a0-8a74-7eab81395197.jpg\" /> </td><td align=\"left\"><h2>Train Wreck Comedy Concert Series presents </h2><h1><span class=\"UnderlineText\">KELLY TAYLOR</span></h1><h2>presented by Prime Time Donair & Poutine</h2></td>
		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Kelly Taylor</span>’s rise through the comedy world has been nothing short of explosive. Just nine short months after stepping on stage for the very first time, Kelly was already headlining clubs — a rare feat that immediately turned heads across the industry. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>In only his second year of comedy, Kelly shocked the Canadian comedy scene by placing second in the prestigious Just For Laughs Homegrown Competition, competing against comedians with more than a decade of experience. His breakout performance caught the attention of major industry players, including NBC Universal, Happy Gilmore Productions, and Jimmy Kimmel’s team, all expressing immediate interest in the rising star. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>That same year, Kelly toured the Canadian college circuit and was crowned Canadian College Comedian of the Year. After quickly conquering stages across Canada, he expanded south of the border and became one of the busiest comedians on the American college scene. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Kelly also starred in the lead role of the feature film <span class=\"ItalicText\">Sure Shot Dombrowski</span>, showcasing his versatility both on stage and on screen. With the ability to headline comedy clubs, corporate events, and colleges just a few years into his career, Kelly Taylor proved early on that he was the real deal. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>In addition to Just For Laughs, Kelly has appeared at both the Vancouver Comedy Festival and the Halifax Comedy Festival, while performing across North America — including standout appearances in Los Angeles and New York City at some of the industry’s most respected comedy clubs. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>A true road warrior, Kelly has toured coast-to-coast across Canada, performed in 46 U.S. states, and brought his comedy overseas to audiences throughout Europe and Asia. He has also proudly performed for the troops in Kuwait, Thailand, Oman, and Afghanistan. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Energetic, sharp, and effortlessly likable, Kelly Taylor continues to win over audiences everywhere he performs. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Pricing</h2><span class=\"BoldText\">Regular  $65.00</span>  ($54.16 base price + $2.36 CIF + $8.48 service charge)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All above prices are CAD and include GST.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">The Train Wreck Comedy Concert Series is bringing five unforgettable nights of world-class stand-up comedy to the Rotary Centre for the Arts, featuring some of the funniest professional comedians from across North America. <span class=\"BoldText\">Freddy’s Brewpub is proud to be the Official Beer Sponsor</span> of the series, serving great local craft beer at all five performances while audiences enjoy razor-sharp storytelling, side-splitting crowd work, huge energy, big personalities, and nonstop laughs.  Whether you're a die-hard comedy fan or just looking for an incredible night out, this is the must-see comedy event series of the year!</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Mary Irwin Theatre at the Rotary Centre for the Arts event tickets include a $2.36 Capital Improvement Fee (CIF). A service fee is added for box office costs, card processing, and taxes. <span class=\"BoldText\">Kelly Taylor</span> tickets and their applicable fees are non-refundable.</span>
""";
