<http://www.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/event/388802AQTLLMRCHTQDTDMKJQHCJSQLVPH>
  a schema:Event;
  schema:name "Train Wreck Comedy Concert Series - Lachlan Patterson";
  schema:description """
	<table class=\" BorderOn\">
		<tr>
			<td align=\"left\" colspan=\"1\"><img src=\"https://system.spektrix.com/kelownacommunitytheatre/files/a70fb740-b316-4389-b1ba-2ef59c38f1f4.jpg\" /> </td><td align=\"left\"><h2>Train Wreck Comedy Concert Series presents </h2><h1><span class=\"UnderlineText\">LACHLAN PATTERSON</span></h1><h2>presented by Prime Time Donair & Poutine</h2></td>
		</tr>
	</table><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Lachlan Patterson</span> is a veteran stand-up comedian whose sharp, offbeat style and effortless delivery have made him a favorite with audiences around the world. Best known for his breakout run on NBC’s <span class=\"ItalicText\">Last Comic Standing</span>, Lachlan battled through a field of more than 1,000 comedians to finish as the show’s runner-up, cementing his place as one of comedy’s most respected performers. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>With a career spanning more than 25 years, Lachlan has built an international following through his smart, relatable comedy that connects with audiences of all ages — and occasionally even their pets. Originally from Vancouver, BC, he now tours globally and regularly shares the stage with comedy heavyweights including Nate Bargatze, Daniel Tosh, and Russell Peters. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Lachlan’s television credits include appearances on <span class=\"ItalicText\">The Tonight Show</span>, <span class=\"ItalicText\">The Late Late Show</span>, Comedy Central’s <span class=\"ItalicText\">Tosh.0</span>, and FX’s <span class=\"ItalicText\">Legit</span>. He has also released three comedy albums on Spotify along with two full-length comedy specials available on Amazon and YouTube. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>His latest special, <span class=\"ItalicText\">Dark White</span>, showcases a more personal side of Lachlan, diving into the life experiences and challenges that have shaped him — all delivered with his signature laid-back charm and razor-sharp wit. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Whether performing in theaters, clubs, festivals, or on screen, Lachlan Patterson continues to prove why he’s regarded as one of the most consistently funny and versatile voices in stand-up comedy today. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><h2>Pricing</h2><span class=\"BoldText\">Regular  $65.00</span>  ($54.16 base price + $2.36 CIF + $8.48 service charge)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">All above prices are CAD and include GST.</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The Train Wreck Comedy Concert Series is bringing five unforgettable nights of world-class stand-up comedy to the Rotary Centre for the Arts, featuring some of the funniest professional comedians from across North America. <span class=\"BoldText\">Freddy’s Brewpub is proud to be the Official Beer Sponsor</span> of the series, serving great local craft beer at all five performances while audiences enjoy razor-sharp storytelling, side-splitting crowd work, huge energy, big personalities, and nonstop laughs.  Whether you're a die-hard comedy fan or just looking for an incredible night out, this is the must-see comedy event series of the year!<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>---<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\">Mary Irwin Theatre at the Rotary Centre for the Arts event tickets include a $2.36 Capital Improvement Fee (CIF). A service fee is added for box office costs, card processing, and taxes. <span class=\"BoldText\">Lachlan Patterson</span> tickets and their applicable fees are non-refundable.</span>
""";
